<br>
R.A. Salvatore is a  wonderfull writer..   He really drew a crowd back to AD&amp;D with his books..   Authors like Salvatore, Cunningham, and Greenwood MADE Forgotten Realms  what it is..   Gary Gygax created the Drow  but R.A.Salvatore put life into them<br>
<br>
The authors who write teh Forgotten Realms books  write them to grab you the moment you open them..  The books may not build up an epic in a single book but if you read teh Forgotten Realms series of books the story is more or less  never ending..<br>
<br>
Authors like Robert Jordan and Terry Brooks  write more epic novels  for those who love all the nuiances of teh world.  Jordan , while his books seem slow are VERY well written and really immerse you into the world he writes about<br>
<br>
BOTH are outstanding authors ..  different styles for different readers  <br>
<br>
honestly  for me though   there are three huge influences that really drew me to RPG   <br>
<br>
J.R. Tolkein<br>
Gary Gygax<br>
R.A. Salvatore<br>
<br>
