<br>
My honest opinion.  If you're looking for a literary masterpiece, read Moby Dick.  If you're looking for a good story, pick up most any book by Salvatore.<br>
<br>
The only books I haven't really enjoyed are the Mortalis set.  I liked the demon war trillogy, but the followup set are just too... dark.  Too depressing.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, though... I love his work, and always pick up his latest books.  And I will likely continue to do so. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/b_angel517/images/anseu.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takkonsmakafu>Takkon Smakafu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 333<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/03 2:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4743.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RA Salvatore on FV!</span><hr size=1> Wow, helluva bump on this thread<br>
